datastructures.symbol_tables

Class DualArrayOrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.symbol_tables.ST<Key,Value>
      • datastructures.symbol_tables.OrderedST<Key,Value>
        • datastructures.symbol_tables.DualArrayOrderedST<Key,Value>

  • public class DualArrayOrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>
extends OrderedST<Key,Value>
    DualArrayOrderedST is a OrderedST which uses two parallel arrays for keys and values. It is based on the implementation used in the book "Algorithms, 4th ed.", by Sedgewick and Wayne.
    Since:
    November 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
    See Also:
    "Algorithms, 4th ed., Robert Sedgewick and Kevin Wayne."

      • rank

        public int rank(Key key)
        Central method for DualArrayOrderedSTs. This method implements binary search for the rank of the provided key. If the key is in the table, it returns its rank (the number of keys that are "smaller than" they key). If it is not in the table, it essentially returns the size of the table.
        Specified by:
        rank in class OrderedST<Key extends java.lang.Comparable<Key>,Value>
        Parameters:
        key - The key to return the rank of.
        Returns:
        the rank of the given key.
